latestIgtvVideos.title: 🌟 Night Time Skincare 🌟 (Tap the caption for more details)
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
A good skincare regime is very important for healthy and glowing skin.
Read below for the basic steps.
**Scroll to the end for Product Details.**
Step 1: Cleanser
Never forget to cleanse your face at the end of the day. It removes all the dirt built up on your face.
Step 2: Face Scrub
Exfoliating your face helps to remove the stubborn dirt and cleans your pores. It’s an optional step. DO NOT use more than 2-3 times a week or you’ll strip away all the moisture from your skin causing oiliness.
Step 3: Toner
After cleansing, it’s important to use a toner. It helps to close the open pores and wipes off any leftover product or dirt.
Step 4: Emulsion/Essence/Serum
An emulsion or serum helps to slow down the process of skin ageing and leaves your skin glowing and nourished.
Step 5: Night cream
Night creams provide additional moisture and keep your skin hydrated throughout the night.
Oily skin fam, you can skip the moisturiser because the emulsion will give you just the right amount of hydration.
Step 6: Lip Balm
Most of us are guilty of licking our lips when they feel dry or chapped. Trust me, stop that habit right away!
The enzymes in your saliva break down the skin on your lips causing furthermore dryness.
Use a lip balm instead and be always kiss-ready! 💋

latestPosts.caption:
Coolest hack I’ve ever tried 🤌🏻

For the girlies who don’t have anything blingy in their closet but don’t want to wear just basics either 🫣

If you don’t have a dewy setting spray, mix some glitter/highlighter in your perfume/mist and it’ll give the same effect 😉

Plus, it washes off easily and you get your basic fit back. 

PS - This hack works on hair too but use a hair mist instead of perfumes/setting sprays 🙌🏻

Enjoy NYE my loves! ❤️
